text = "[font_size=20][center][b]Automatic transition[/b][/center][/font_size]

You can set transition event to \"Auto\" , which makes it an automatic transition. Automatic transition is also called eventless transition, since the actual event it response is null.

Parsing null event to step the statechart won't touch any automatic transition. Actually statechart ignores parsed null event. Automatic transitions are used automatically in every normal step, after statechart has selected and executed non-eventless transitions with parsed event.

Here in this test:

[ol]
Initially, we have Root/A/X active. But at this point statechart is not stepped yet, so automatic transition A/X/(Auto)->Y is not touched. You'll see exit of A/X as you step.
In first step, transition A/->B is executed so A/X is exit and B/X is entered. In the moment, B/X/(Auto)->Y is selected and executed, so B/X is exit and B/Y is entered.
In second step, we transit back to A/X. This time A/X/(Auto)->Y is executed, so A/X is exit and A/Y is entered immediately.
[/ol]
"

